  "texts": [
    "For any s ∈ P(I):⌢ A s = {a ∈ A| π a (a) = s}, A s = {a ∈ A| π a (a) ⊃ s} = ⊔{ ⌢ A t ∶ t ⊃ s}.",
    "Knit and Nerve of a p-siteIn this subsection we establish the main relationships between the p-sites (the objects of the P-foundation) and p-formations (the objects of the Pconfiguration).",
    "In particular we show how any p-site with base I induces a couple of interesting complexes on I, say (S, K) such that K -= S and how conversely, to any such couple of complexes, we can associate, in a canonical way, a p-site that in turn induces precisely those very complexes.",
    "(ii) the Nerve of a:σ a ∶= {s ∈ P 0 (I)|A s ≠ ∅} = {s ∈ P 0 (I)| ∃a ∈ A, s ⊂ π a (a)}.",
    "▽Note that the Nerve of a is a simplicial complex, therefore (I, σ a) is a p-structure."
